physical_appearance: This is a collection of aquatint illustrations of battle scenes set against the Burmese landscape during the first Anglo-Burmese War in 1824.
sgcool_label_text: This collection of aquatint illustrations of the first Anglo-Burmese War in 1824. The prints were based on original drawings by Lieutenant Joseph Moore, a senior naval officer of the 89th Regiment, and dedicated to the Court of Directors of the British East India Company.
title_text: Eighteen Views at and Near Rangoon by Lieutenant Joseph Moore
subject_terms_2: Anglo-Burmese War, 1st, 1824-1826 Moore, Joseph, Lieutenant Aquatint Drawing Burma  Great Britain  Battles in art East India Company  Navies Officers
